{"article_id":"CovREkCydwm4w05T","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"\" Talk to Joe Biden and McConnell , \"","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"Mr. Reid told reporters","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"when asked","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"if negotiations were continuing .","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"In the balance are more than a half-trillion dollars in tax increases on virtually every working American and across-the-board spending cuts","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"that are scheduled to begin Tuesday .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"Taken together ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"they threaten to push the economy back into recession .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"\" It looks awful , \"","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"said Senator Richard J. Durbin of Illinois , the second-ranking Democrat .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"\" I ' m sure","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"the American people are saying ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"with so much at stake why are they waiting so late","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"to get this done ? \"","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"Senator Lindsey Graham , Republican of South Carolina ,","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"who had said early Sunday","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"that he thought","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"a deal was within reach ,","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"said later on his Twitter feed ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"\" I think","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"we ' re going over the cliff . \"","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"Weeks of negotiations between President Obama and Speaker John A. Boehner inched toward a deal","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"to avert the so-called fiscal cliff ,","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"while locking in trillions of dollars in deficit reduction over 10 years","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"and starting an effort","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"to overhaul the tax code and entitlement programs like Medicare .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"But earlier this month , Mr. Boehner walked away from those talks .","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"Instead he tried to reach a much more modest deal","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"to avoid a fiscal crisis","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"by extending the expiring tax cuts for incomes under $ 1 million .","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"When Mr. Boehner ' s own Republican members revolted ,","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"he ceded negotiations to the Senate .","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"But compromise has proved equally elusive in that chamber .","depth":4},{"id":33,"text":"Absent a last-minute deal , Mr. Reid is expected to move on Monday to bring to a vote a stopgap measure","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"pushed by Mr. Obama ,","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"which would retain lower tax rates for incomes below $ 250,000","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"and extend unemployment benefits .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"But it was not clear","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"that would even get a vote .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"The objection of a single senator on Monday would run out the clock on the 112th Congress","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"before a final tally could be taken .","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"Mr. Obama appeared on the NBC program \" Meet the Press \" on Sunday","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"and implored Congress to act .","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"\" We have been talking to the Republicans","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"ever since the election was over , \"","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Mr. Obama said in the interview .","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"\" They have had trouble saying yes to a number of repeated offers . \"","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"After the talks broke down over the inflation demand ,","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"Senate Republicans emerged from a closed-door meeting on Sunday afternoon","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"to declare the issue off the table for now .","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"Senator John McCain , Republican of Arizona , said","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"that holding the line","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"against raising taxes on high-income households","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"while fighting for cuts to Social Security","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"was \" not a winning hand . \"","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"Newsletter Sign Up","depth":5},{"id":56,"text":"Continue reading the main story","depth":5},{"id":57,"text":"Please verify","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"you 're not a robot","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"by clicking the box .","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"Invalid email address .","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"Please re-enter .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"You must select a newsletter","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"to subscribe to .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"Sign Up","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"You will receive emails","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"containing news content , updates and promotions from The New York Times .","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"You may opt-out at any time .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"You agree to receive occasional updates and special offers for The New York Times 's products and services .","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"Thank you for subscribing .","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"An error has occurred .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"Please try again later .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"View all New York Times newsletters .","depth":3},{"id":73,"text":"Then they mustered a new talking point ,","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"saying","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"Democrats want to raise taxes","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"only to spend more money .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"Their new objection :","depth":7},{"id":78,"text":"Democrats are seeking a one- to two-year \" pause \" for across-the-board spending cuts and an extension of expired unemployment benefits for two million people .","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"\" We raise taxes ,","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"and we spend more ? \"","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"asked Senator Kay Bailey Hutchison , Republican of Texas .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"\" It ' s business as usual . \"","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"For their part , Democrats beat back the inflation proposal ,","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"and then promptly proclaimed themselves incensed","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"that Republicans would not soften their position on a generous level of taxation on inherited estates and an insistence","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"that a final deal permanently prevent the alternative minimum tax , a parallel tax system","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"meant to ensure","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"that wealthy people pay more ,","depth":11},{"id":89,"text":"from expanding","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"to affect more of the middle class .","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"Democrats were also demanding","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"that across-the-board cuts to military and domestic programs","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"- known as the \" sequester \" -","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"at least be delayed .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"\" We ' re not here","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"to defend government ,","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"we ' re here","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"to make sure of the defense of our country , \"","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"said Senator Barbara A. Mikulski , Democrat of Maryland ,","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"whose state would be hit particularly hard .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"\" Sequester has consequences . \"","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"Senate Democratic aides were openly making legislative plans for later this week ,","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"to press Democratic proposals","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"after the fiscal deadline is breached","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"- and after the next Congress is sworn in on Thursday with more Democrats in both the House and the Senate .","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"But officials close to the negotiations said","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"the talks were continuing ,","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"centered for now on a new axis , Mr. McConnell and Mr. Biden .","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"Much of the umbrage was oddly discordant .","depth":6},{"id":110,"text":"Mr. Obama has long advocated for a permanent fix to the alternative minimum tax ,","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"which must be \" patched \" each year","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"to keep it from applying to middle-income families .","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"Until this weekend , both Democrats and Republicans appeared willing to let the across-the-board cuts take effect , at least temporarily ,","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"while a larger deficit deal is negotiated early next year .","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"Indeed , many Republicans were the loudest in protesting the cuts .","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"Now that Democrats want them canceled ,","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"Republicans equate that position to raising taxes","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"in order to spend more .","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"On some of the biggest sticking points , the two sides are now inches apart .","depth":6},{"id":120,"text":"Barely a week after House Republicans refused to vote to allow taxes to rise on incomes over $ 1 million ,","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"Senate Republicans proposed","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"allowing tax rates to rise on incomes over $ 450,000 for individuals and $ 550,000 for couples .","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"Democrats countered with a proposal","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"to extend expiring Bush-era tax cuts up to $ 360,000 for individuals and $ 450,000 for couples .","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"For both sides , that meant major movement .","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"Mr. Obama has been holding firm at a $ 250,000 threshold .","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"Of course , a big question hung over the negotiations in the Senate :","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"even if the Senate can find an accord ,","depth":10},{"id":129,"text":"would it pass the House ?","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"Even on the estate tax , the two sides are not far apart ,","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"although their language is .","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"Republicans want to tax estates","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"valued above $ 5 million","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"at 35 percent .","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"Democrats want to tax inheritances above $ 3.5 million at 45 percent .","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"If that sounds like a bridgeable divide ,","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"Democrats are not conceding an inch .","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"\" The net result is that 6,000 Americans would get a $ 1-million-a-year tax break on their estate tax , \"","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"Mr. Durbin said .","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"\" The Republicans once again are ready to shut us down over not 2 percent of the population , but 0.1 percent of the population . \"","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":281,"left":195,"right":280,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":195,"left":161,"right":194,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":144,"right":160,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":0,"right":143,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":1,"right":142,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":160,"left":147,"right":159,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":145,"right":146,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":159,"left":152,"right":158,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":152,"left":148,"right":151,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":10,"right":150,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":150,"left":11,"right":149,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":149,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"paren